title: Corrections & Amplifications
text:
Kavitha Prasad, who oversees Intel Corp.'s artificial intelligence strategy, previously worked at a machine-learning startup where she was an early employee. An article about Intel in the April 11 Journal Report on Artificial Intelligence incorrectly said she co-founded the startup.

(See: "Artificial Intelligence (A Special Report)

---

Inside Intel's AI-Chip Strategy: The company has lagged behind Nvidia in the fast-growing segment. It's determined to reverse that." -- WSJ Apr. 11, 2022)
